# Tiger Style

Source: https://tigerstyle.dev/
Full reference: https://github.com/tigerbeetle/tigerbeetle/blob/main/docs/TIGER_STYLE.md

Priority order: Safety > Performance > Developer Experience.

## Safety

- Minimum 2 assertions per function: validate arguments on entry, validate return values before exit.
- No recursion without provable termination.
- All loops have explicit upper bounds. Assert bounds are not exceeded.
- No dynamic allocation after initialization in performance-critical paths.
- Every error is handled explicitly. No silent discard.
- Zero external dependencies unless strictly necessary.

## Performance

- Sketch performance budget (network, disk, memory, compute) before implementing non-trivial functions.
- Batch operations to amortize per-call costs.
- Separate control plane from data plane.
- No allocation in hot paths.

## Code Structure

- Functions: 70 lines maximum.
- Names include units and qualifiers: `timeout_ms`, `size_bytes`, `is_valid`, `count_max`.
- snake_case throughout.
- No abbreviations except well-established domain terms.
- No global mutable state.

## Zero Technical Debt

Fix problems during design. Do not defer correctness to production.
